WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.565
Come on, let's just go to the marina, we'll rent a sail boat

00:03.630 --> 00:05.200
and spend the whole day on the water.

00:05.260 --> 00:06.460
Hey. Please, stop it.

00:06.530 --> 00:08.560
It's not fair, ok, to Delia.

00:08.930 --> 00:10.360
We haven't been out in 3 days,

00:10.430 --> 00:12.560
And she's, you know, at the store alone.

00:12.630 --> 00:14.000
3 days? What's that?

00:14.060 --> 00:16.200
After what we've been through, we deserve a week.

00:16.200 --> 00:17.770
Look, why don't we take the train to ocean city?

00:17.800 --> 00:19.270
There's that little inn we used to go to.

00:19.340 --> 00:21.870
We could spend the whole day there by ourselves.

00:22.840 --> 00:23.770
What's wrong?

00:24.640 --> 00:27.200
Nothing. It's just...

00:27.270 --> 00:29.800
Waking up with you and talking to you,

00:29.870 --> 00:31.970
I never thought I'd get to do that again.

00:37.500 --> 00:39.140
Well, we're doing it.

00:40.870 --> 00:42.305
I'm not going anywhere.

00:42.305 --> 00:43.740
We just have to get back to normal.

00:43.800 --> 00:45.300
Normal?

00:49.500 --> 00:53.040
All right,guys. Let's unload this equipment.

00:54.700 --> 00:57.000
Little redecorating, and this'll work just fine.

00:57.070 --> 00:59.200
Oh, what about the town square out front?

00:59.270 --> 01:00.670
- It's available until midnight.  - Perfect.

01:00.740 --> 01:03.370
What's going on, and who are these people?

01:03.440 --> 01:06.070
Ok, you'll never believe. That is Cally O'Keefe.

01:06.140 --> 01:09.470
She is the creator and the head writer of Hope's Edge...

01:09.540 --> 01:12.370
And they wanna film right here in the store.

01:12.440 --> 01:13.700
Hope's Edge?

01:13.770 --> 01:14.900
Yeah, the soap opera.

01:14.970 --> 01:16.940
Uh, I used to watch it at the station with the guys.

01:17.000 --> 01:20.140
Well,F.Y.I., she prefers Daytime serial.

01:20.200 --> 01:22.000
I think we should get rid of all of those here...

01:22.070 --> 01:23.300
And she's directing this one.

01:23.370 --> 01:25.270
Apparently it's the tenth anniversary of the show.

01:25.340 --> 01:27.600
They're filming the whole thing right here in Grandview.

01:27.670 --> 01:29.970
Hello. Back to earth. Did you actually say yes?

01:30.040 --> 01:31.040
No. Of course not.

01:31.100 --> 01:32.040
We can always tell her no.

01:32.100 --> 01:33.370
I just think it would be

01:33.440 --> 01:34.770
great publicity for the store.

01:34.840 --> 01:36.140
Yeah,but what's gonna be left of the store

01:36.140 --> 01:37.440
when they're done?

01:37.500 --> 01:39.000
Eh,good point.

01:39.070 --> 01:41.200
Hey,Cal. Hmm?

01:41.270 --> 01:43.440
Oh...my...

01:43.500 --> 01:44.440
God.

01:44.500 --> 01:45.440
Oh, my god.

01:45.500 --> 01:46.570
Easy,kid

01:46.640 --> 01:48.670
Can we talk about the scene in the cemetery?

01:48.740 --> 01:50.040
The language feels a little cruel.

01:50.100 --> 01:52.000
Well, you're not yourself, remember?

01:52.070 --> 01:53.440
Look,just...just give me 2 seconds,

01:53.500 --> 01:54.200
and we'll talk about it.

01:54.270 --> 01:56.140
Who is that?

01:56.200 --> 01:58.070
You are so hopeless.

01:58.140 --> 01:59.600
That is Grant Harper.

01:59.670 --> 02:01.570
Yeah,he plays the surgeon on the show.

02:01.640 --> 02:03.700
Yeah, and he just got diagnosed with this brain tumor,

02:03.770 --> 02:05.340
so he's having blackouts all the time.

02:05.400 --> 02:06.770
Oh, my god, and he's still working?

02:06.840 --> 02:07.740
Oh. No, not on the...

02:07.800 --> 02:09.539
No, it's his character on the show.

02:09.600 --> 02:11.240
He plays Dr. Troy Dolden, right?

02:11.300 --> 02:12.670
So he has this on-again, off-again

02:12.740 --> 02:13.670
love-hate relationship

02:13.740 --> 02:14.900
- with Celeste... - Celeste.

02:14.970 --> 02:17.140
Barrington, and... she's the owner of the hospital.

02:17.200 --> 02:18.940
And he has these blackouts, and he...he becomes evil,

02:19.000 --> 02:20.770
but he can't remember after it happens.

02:20.840 --> 02:23.770
I... It's really addictive.

02:24.770 --> 02:26.040
Yeah, I...I just don't think the fans

02:26.100 --> 02:27.770
Wanna hear me talk to Celeste that way.

02:27.840 --> 02:28.800
I will look at it. Promise.

02:28.870 --> 02:30.270
Uh, don't you have that photo shoot right now?

02:30.340 --> 02:32.440
- Yeah.  - Come on.

02:32.500 --> 02:34.200
It's perfect.

02:34.270 --> 02:35.240
We'll take it.

02:35.300 --> 02:36.240
Oh. That's, um...

02:36.300 --> 02:37.570
Oh,gosh. Cally, I'm sorry.

02:37.640 --> 02:39.940
This is my business partner I was telling you about.

02:40.000 --> 02:40.940
This is Melinda. Hi.

02:41.000 --> 02:42.100
And this is her, um... wow.

02:42.170 --> 02:43.100
Sam. Sam.

02:43.170 --> 02:46.000
This is Sam. And, uh, this is Duff.

02:46.070 --> 02:47.140
Faraday, first assistant director.

02:47.200 --> 02:48.170
Hello. Nice to meet you.

02:48.240 --> 02:50.440
You have such lovely things in your store.

02:50.500 --> 02:51.670
Oh, well, thank you. Anyway...

02:51.680 --> 02:53.240
Oh, and,Duff, we need to make sure we get these guys

02:53.310 --> 02:55.710
V.I.P. Passes to the thing at the university tonight.

02:55.780 --> 02:56.610
What thing?

02:56.780 --> 02:58.210
An evening with Hope's Edge.

02:58.280 --> 02:59.710
We're screening highlights from the show.

02:59.780 --> 03:01.380
Some of the cast members are gonna do a Q&A.

03:01.440 --> 03:02.810
- Oh, I...I don't know if I... - Cool.

03:02.880 --> 03:03.940
Oh, we would love to go.

03:04.010 --> 03:05.440
Ok. Well, I'm just a little worried

03:05.510 --> 03:06.880
about losing a whole day of business,so...

03:06.940 --> 03:08.910
Compensation's in paragraph 6.

03:08.980 --> 03:11.710
Really? For one day.

03:11.780 --> 03:13.840
Plus a day of prep, with an option to extend,

03:13.910 --> 03:15.380
plus 50% in case Cally goes over schedule.

03:15.440 --> 03:17.580
Nobody's going over schedule.

03:17.640 --> 03:20.210
You know what? Take as long as you need.

03:22.640 --> 03:25.610
So... I haven't seen you much for the past 3 days.

03:25.680 --> 03:27.580
P.S., you're glowing.

03:27.640 --> 03:28.610
Any connection?

03:28.680 --> 03:31.210
Let's just say everything's fine.

03:33.540 --> 03:36.040
Excuse me,sir. You dropped your hat.

03:36.110 --> 03:37.210
I didn't realize...

03:37.280 --> 03:39.880
Eli. Knew it.

03:39.940 --> 03:43.440
Hey,look, they invited the whole faculty, ok?

03:43.510 --> 03:45.280
And my mom's a big fan,

03:45.340 --> 03:47.410
So I thought I'd come down and get an autograph.

03:47.480 --> 03:48.580
Yeah, mm-hmm.

03:48.640 --> 03:51.010
For her. Not for me.

03:51.080 --> 03:53.280
I'm not the only one. See?

03:54.110 --> 03:56.110
Hi-ho,everyone.

03:56.310 --> 03:57.740
I'm Duff Faraday.

03:57.810 --> 03:59.580
And as first assistant director on the show,

03:59.640 --> 04:01.210
It's my job to keep things moving along,

04:01.280 --> 04:04.440
so welcome to an evening with Hope's Edge.

04:05.080 --> 04:08.680
First of all,let's say hello to our exec producer,

04:08.740 --> 04:11.440
creator,head writer, and frequent director,

04:11.510 --> 04:13.640
And, yes, they are all the same person.

04:13.710 --> 04:14.710
Cally O'Keefe!

04:19.110 --> 04:21.010
Thank you, Grandview.

04:21.079 --> 04:23.240
It's a pleasure to be here. I'm...

04:23.310 --> 04:24.910
Oh ho ho. Yes. Yes.

04:24.980 --> 04:26.840
And next up, here they are,

04:26.910 --> 04:28.780
Daytime's dynamic duo.

04:28.840 --> 04:31.010
And, yes, we are introducing them together,

04:31.080 --> 04:32.610
because...whew... wouldn't wanna

04:32.680 --> 04:34.680
Start a fight between these two.

04:35.540 --> 04:36.910
Here they are,

04:36.980 --> 04:39.610
Dr. Troy Holden and Celeste Barrington.

04:39.680 --> 04:42.640
Say hello to Suzanne Zale and Grant Harper!

04:48.640 --> 04:50.480
You see that?

04:50.540 --> 04:51.740
They love me.

04:51.810 --> 04:53.080
Love to hate you, you mean.

04:55.410 --> 04:56.780
Thank you,Duff.

04:56.840 --> 04:59.110
This is such a treat for us.

04:59.180 --> 05:01.180
You know, I actually discovered Grant

05:01.240 --> 05:03.610
right here on this stage when he auditioned

05:03.680 --> 05:06.240
for my first play way back in grad school.

05:08.110 --> 05:10.280
Don't you mean your only play?

05:14.540 --> 05:17.110
So this is an honor for us.

05:17.180 --> 05:18.240
Sorry I'm late.

05:18.310 --> 05:19.540
I was indisposed.

05:19.610 --> 05:21.540
Before we show you highlights from the past

05:21.610 --> 05:23.380
10 seasons of Hope's Edge,

05:23.440 --> 05:25.940
I would like to open things up for your questions.

05:26.010 --> 05:27.640
Oh, this ought to be good.

05:28.880 --> 05:30.480
Yes.

05:30.540 --> 05:32.880
Hi. My name's Janet,

05:32.940 --> 05:34.840
and I'm president of the Grandview chapter

05:34.910 --> 05:36.880
of the Hope's Edge fan club.

05:36.940 --> 05:39.140
And I don't mean to be disrespectful,

05:39.210 --> 05:40.710
but what were you and your writers thinking

05:40.780 --> 05:42.610
when you decided to ruin the character of Dr. Holden?

05:44.780 --> 05:46.340
Excellent question,cal.

05:46.410 --> 05:48.280
That's the whole brain-tumor, blackout thing.

05:48.340 --> 05:48.880
Got it.

05:48.940 --> 05:50.110
To tell you the truth,

05:50.180 --> 05:54.010
after the last 10 years of Dr. Holden being so flawless,

05:54.080 --> 05:56.710
sometimes to keep a story fresh,

05:56.780 --> 05:58.180
you have to take some risks.

05:58.240 --> 06:00.275
And now spoilerfest.com says

06:00.275 --> 06:02.110
you're gonna kill him off for good

06:02.180 --> 06:03.380
Is that true?

06:03.640 --> 06:05.240
Is Grant Harper leaving the show?

06:05.310 --> 06:06.580
- What? - No way.

06:06.640 --> 06:10.210
Look, I don't wanna be confirming or denying rumors...

06:10.210 --> 06:11.280
But I will say,

06:11.340 --> 06:13.480
In TV, there are a lot of reasons

06:13.540 --> 06:15.580
you might have to write a character out...

06:15.640 --> 06:18.080
A salary dispute, an actor breaks out

06:18.140 --> 06:20.080
and the network wants to give them their own series,

06:20.140 --> 06:25.580
or sometimes the actor just wants a change.

06:25.640 --> 06:29.180
And in any of those circumstances,

06:29.240 --> 06:31.510
you might have to kill the actor.

06:31.580 --> 06:33.910
Well, you guys know a thing or two about that.

06:36.980 --> 06:39.440
Ok, ok, we were gonna save this for the end,

06:39.510 --> 06:41.680
but, uh, look on the back of your programs.

06:41.740 --> 06:43.540
There's a form where you can enter a contest

06:43.610 --> 06:47.280
To win a walk-on part on our 10th anniversary special.

06:47.340 --> 06:48.640
No,here. Wait, I wanna do it!

06:48.710 --> 06:50.240
A part in the show. No way.

06:50.310 --> 06:52.010
You guys check that out, and we'll, uh, roll the video.

06:52.080 --> 06:52.660
Thank you.

06:53.700 --> 06:58.240
Rolling, any second now. Video.

07:01.480 --> 07:04.410
We got a surprise guest.

07:06.010 --> 07:08.540
Players are in place.

07:09.380 --> 07:11.010
Stage is set.

07:11.010 --> 07:14.010
Just no video? Tell you why. You...

07:16.222 --> 07:17.916
- What's wrong with the lights? - What's with the lights?

07:18.316 --> 07:20.010
Guys, guys

07:20.080 --> 07:21.680
Just a moment, ladies and gentlemen.

07:21.740 --> 07:24.780
We're experiencing some technical difficulties.

07:29.740 --> 07:31.910
And now someone's gonna go out with a bang.

